Description: Fragment of the corner of a cavetto cornice
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Very probably from the "Qasr", passage between the two casemate buildings A and B, or west side of casemate building
Curator's comments: Very probably the "cornice... around the top of ...wall" of the open-air court at the entrance of the casemate building B of the "Qasr", or one of the "pieces of cornice with ordinary Egyptian cavetto moulding" found on the west of casemate building B, mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 56 § 55.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 56 § 55)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.43, p.55, p.176, pl.18)
